README.rst
     1Ôćĺ====================================================
     2Ôćĺpluggy - A minimalist production ready plugin system
     3Ôćĺ====================================================
     4Ôćĺ
     5Ôćĺ|pypi| |conda-forge| |versions| |github-actions| |gitter| |black| |codecov|
     6Ôćĺ
     7ÔćĺThis is the core framework used by the `pytest`_, `tox`_, and `devpi`_ projects.
     8Ôćĺ
     9ÔćĺPlease `read the docs`_ to learn more!
    10Ôćĺ
    11ÔćĺA definitive example
    12Ôćĺ====================
    13Ôćĺ.. code-block:: python
    14Ôćĺ
    15Ôćĺ    import pluggy
    16Ôćĺ
    17Ôćĺ    hookspec = pluggy.HookspecMarker("myproject")
    18Ôćĺ    hookimpl = pluggy.HookimplMarker("myproject")
    19Ôćĺ
    20Ôćĺ
    21Ôćĺ    class MySpec:
    22Ôćĺ        """A hook specification namespace."""
    23Ôćĺ
    24Ôćĺ        @hookspec
    25Ôćĺ        def myhook(self, arg1, arg2):
    26Ôćĺ            """My special little hook that you can customize."""
    27Ôćĺ
    28Ôćĺ
    29Ôćĺ    class Plugin_1:
    30Ôćĺ        """A hook implementation namespace."""
    31Ôćĺ
    32Ôćĺ        @hookimpl
    33Ôćĺ        def myhook(self, arg1, arg2):
    34Ôćĺ            print("inside Plugin_1.myhook()")
    35Ôćĺ            return arg1 + arg2
    36Ôćĺ
    37Ôćĺ
    38Ôćĺ    class Plugin_2:
    39Ôćĺ        """A 2nd hook implementation namespace."""
    40Ôćĺ
    41Ôćĺ        @hookimpl
    42Ôćĺ        def myhook(self, arg1, arg2):
    43Ôćĺ            print("inside Plugin_2.myhook()")
    44Ôćĺ            return arg1 - arg2
    45Ôćĺ
    46Ôćĺ
    47Ôćĺ    # create a manager and add the spec
    48Ôćĺ    pm = pluggy.PluginManager("myproject")
    49Ôćĺ    pm.add_hookspecs(MySpec)
    50Ôćĺ
    51Ôćĺ    # register plugins
    52Ôćĺ    pm.register(Plugin_1())
    53Ôćĺ    pm.register(Plugin_2())
    54Ôćĺ
    55Ôćĺ    # call our ``myhook`` hook
    56Ôćĺ    results = pm.hook.myhook(arg1=1, arg2=2)
    57Ôćĺ    print(results)
    58Ôćĺ
    59Ôćĺ
    60ÔćĺRunning this directly gets us::
    61Ôćĺ
    62Ôćĺ    $ python docs/examples/toy-example.py
    63Ôćĺ    inside Plugin_2.myhook()
    64Ôćĺ    inside Plugin_1.myhook()
    65Ôćĺ    [-1, 3]
    66Ôćĺ
    67Ôćĺ
    68Ôćĺ.. badges
    69Ôćĺ
